const faqs = [
  {
    question: "Do I need a Facebook Business page?",
    answer: "A Facebook Business page with Messenger activated is required — personal accounts do not support the integration. Extension companies typically maintain active Facebook pages to showcase completed projects, share progress updates, and collect client reviews. The AI adds professional message handling to your existing social presence."
  },
  {
    question: "What extension enquiries come through Messenger?",
    answer: "Almost exclusively domestic leads. Homeowners see your completed extension galleries — open-plan kitchen-diners, bi-fold door reveals, lantern roof interiors — and message asking about pricing, timelines, and whether you are available. These are high-quality prospects who have already judged your work quality and want to engage specifically because they like what they see."
  },
  {
    question: "How quickly does the AI reply on Messenger?",
    answer: "Inside seconds. Messenger shows active indicators, so the homeowner sees immediate engagement from your business. For extension specialists — where homeowners compare portfolios of three to five companies — the speed of your first professional reply often determines who gets invited to measure up."
  },
  {
    question: "What does Facebook Messenger cost?",
    answer: `Facebook Messenger is available at £${pricing.addOn.price}/month as an add-on. Extension specialists handle residential projects spanning £25,000 single-storey rears to £150,000 double-storey wraparounds — winning even the most modest Facebook-sourced extension enquiry through a prompt Messenger reply repays the annual add-on cost from the first project.`
  },
  {
    question: "Can I pick up Messenger conversations?",
    answer: "Typing your own reply in any Messenger thread transfers the conversation to you. The homeowner sees one continuous exchange. Most extension specialists let the AI handle the initial scope capture and follow up personally to discuss design details, arrange the site visit, and provide a quote."
  },
  {
    question: "How is Messenger data protected?",
    answer: "All Messenger conversations, kitchen photos, extension dimensions, planning details, and homeowner contact information are encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Data is delivered to you alone and is never disclosed to competitors, sold to lead brokers, or repurposed for advertising."
  }
